          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4siwmQ7JKF8MvCZkJce2dWDVi2tVq8eoHTAzVjl2NjB38qA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "one star.\n\nabsolutely ridiculous experience at cvs today. i went in clearly sick just trying to buy dayquil, something completely normal, and the cashier refused to sell it to me. i am 20 years old, which is well above the legal age of 18 required to purchase it. when i told him that and even offered to show my id, he straight up told me that even if i had my id he still wouldn\u2019t sell it to me because i\u2019m \u201cnot 21.\u201d\n\nsince when did cvs employees start making up their own laws? the law says 18, not 21. i wasn\u2019t trying to buy alcohol or cigarettes, i was trying to buy cold medicine because i\u2019m sick.\n\nhis exact reasoning was basically that i\u2019m \u201cnot old enough for him to let me buy it.\u201d so apparently personal opinions now override actual laws and store policy. incredibly unprofessional and honestly just rude.\n\nif your employees don\u2019t know the basic rules about the products they\u2019re selling, maybe train them before putting them on the register. all i wanted was medicine and instead got someone on a power trip who decided to enforce rules that don\u2019t even exist.\n\none star. do better.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2toU1JFbHdTa05VUTFRNVJVSkhRbUZDVnpjd1FWRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x3628d1a2c35f8fc7!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkhSRElwSkNUQ1Q5RUJHQmFCVzcwQVE%7C%7C?hl=en",
